Target has better quality BUT this is a better deal and since ours only last a few months anyway from either location - this is a great bargain.

reviews.title: What is in the fibers of this mat?
reviews.review_text: I liked the size and the design, but the material was awful. It has some very odd fibers in it that are a rust/brown color that isn't very noticeable at first. But after setting it out on my patio, it started turning my patio “rusty”. I looked at the back and it seemed fine. So I cleaned my patio, only to find this outdoor mat turned my patio reddish brown colors again! When I looked at it closer, you can see some thick fiber type material in it that is almost like little pieces of beef jerky in texture. I used some tweezers to try and pick them out, but they left holes in the mat, and there's far too many to try and get them all out. It's just…..gross. And it has an odd odor to it also. I would not ever recommend this outdoor mat to anyone. Also, it allows me to show a picture of how it turned my patio colors, but not allowing me to show pictures of the actual mat!!

reviews.title: I love it!

reviews.title: durable
reviews.review_text: I decided to replace my current door mat because I was looking for a more appealing design to add some décor to my front door area. I was attracted to the color and the printed Hello word of this doormat. I didn't realize how thick this was until I removed it from the box. Mainstays Coir Hello 18 x 30 doormat is thick, sturdy and feels like it would hold up really well. One thing that I noticed immediately when I unpacked it was all the loose tiny straws all over the box and on my floor. I was afraid that the fiber of the rug would be brought into the house. I had to shake the rug multiple times to make sure to remove all the loose straws. This seems to work because I have been using this rug for a couple of weeks and I had no straws in the house. Overall, if you are looking to replace your mat and want a strong and durable mat, this one will work. I am happy with my Hello doormat. I recommend it.
